6. Are saliva tests more reliable than urine tests? Saliva tests are non-invasive and provide quicker results, though urine tests are often considered more comprehensive.

7. Can saliva tests detect all types of drugs? No, certain substances are harder to detect in saliva, limiting the scope of the tests.

